"Teenage Kicks" is a 1978 song originally recorded by Irish punk rock group The Undertones. Composed by the band&#039;s principal songwriter, John O&#039;Neill, it was championed by DJ John Peel, and was his all-time favourite song.The Teenage Kicks EP was produced by Dave Smyth, who produced many of the Good Vibrations records in the 1970s, at his studio, Wizard Sound Studios in Belfast.
"Teenage Kicks" was acoustically covered by Snow Patrol in tribute to John Peel, and was played at his funeral.
